Meet <b>Lulu</b>, our citizen of the week!<br><br>Lulu lives at <a href='/home/?user=judyblueeyes'>12202 Wild Rose Road</a>, in the historical neighborhood of Ravenwood.  She has been a citizen since December 14th of 2004, and has been greatly enjoying her time in Millsberry.<br><br>Lulu is a curious and clever girl, who does very well in her classes at Millsberry Academy.  She's especially well known for her observational skills, which come in handy during lab projects in Mr. Fort's science class.<br><br>After school, Lulu often enjoys some quiet time, relaxing and reading in her room.  When she is feeling creative, though, Lulu likes to draw in her sketchbook.  She's actually getting quite good!  Occasionally she'll add a little color to her drawings with some colored pencils she received for her birthday last year.  Most of the time, the subjects of her drawings turn out to be gray, silver, or indigo (which isn't surprising, considering that those are her favorite colors).  Lulu often listens to music while drawing,  more often than not, to a CD of jazz, showtunes, or new wave songs.<br><br>During the weekend, Lulu likes to leave the house and get some fresh air.  She'll often head northwest to Lakeview, where she enjoys sailing around Millsberry Lake when it's summer.  Now that it's winter, though, and the lake is frozen, she delights in ice-skating on its surface with other students from Millsberry Academy.<br><br>Another of Lulu's favorite spots is the zoo, where she enjoys watching (and sometimes sketching) the animals.  After a busy day walking around and enjoying her favorite activities, Lulu likes to head down to Regio's famous pizza parlor for a delicious dinner. <br><br>Lulu has recently been working on upgrades to her house, such as adding yards for her two new dogs from The Pet Palace and beautifully decorating her home's interior.  Next time you're in Ravenwood, be sure to stop by and say hello to this wonderful citizen!</div>
